Cell.Text: G|Stay close and in plain view. No funny business unless you want a few inches of steel in your belly.
If there's someone in the palace who can speak for you and wouldn't mind walking you around. Great. Lead me to him.

Node.Caption: DA02SomeoneElse: Perhaps one of my friends here in the palace could be my escort?

Cell.Text: I suppose you're free to frolic with the wenches in the servants quarters, but anywhere else, you must have an escort. Jarl's orders.
Yes, the Steward is taking visitors. However, I must accompany you at all times while on the royal premises.

Node.Caption: DA02Steward: Perhaps I could speak with the Steward instead?

Cell.Text: I'm afraid you'll have to come back later. I've been given strict instructions that no one be allowed to trouble Lady Elisif.

Node.Caption: DA02PressingBusiness: That won't do. I have pressing business for the Jarl.

Cell.Text: [S] S|I've been instructed to tell all visitors that the Lady Elisif isn't feeling well. She wishes you a good day, and please call again another time.
Yes. Are you enjoying our little walk together? Or perhaps you'd like to come back when the Lady is taking visitors?
She's telling everyone she's sick. But she's really locked herself in her room because she fears an assassin is out to get her.

She's locked herself in her room not letting anyone in. Well, except for us servants. She's afraid of assassins coming to get her. | Even still, I make a point of announcing myself when I enter her room now. I spooked her so bad last time she almost threw the chamber pot at me!
I know. The poor girl's fright has left her bereft of reason. But there's no talking her out of it. I fear she'll be locked in there for days.
Not so ridiculous, really. I know people don't think much of her. But she is the Jarl after all. Plenty of folk would kill to be in her shoes.

Node.Caption: DA02ThatsCrazy: An assassin, really? That's ridiculous. Who would want to kill her?

Cell.Text: [S] G|I bet she would feel safer. And hopefully you wouldn't have to baby sit her for long. Once she calms down, she might start thinking straight again. | Let's go talk with her. Stay close. Talk of assassins have the guards jumpy. They might attack you if you're not standing near me.
She let's the servants in? Seems like a gap in security that could be exploited.

Well, she needs to eat. I don't think she even knows where the kitchen is. And I dare say, milady isn't going to carry her own piss out, is she now? | It hardly matters though. The door to the stairs is securely locked. There's no way anyone without the key can get in. So don't you worry about it.

Node.Caption: DA02Favor: Maybe she'd feel safer with a personal body guard? I could do that.

Cell.Text: [S] G|I suppose so. But believe me. Only us servants have a key like that, and its a very expensive looking lock. Really, I wouldn't worry about it. | Here. Take a look for yourself. But give it back soon. It's almost time for milady's medicine.

Node.Caption: DA02Key: Not all locks are of the highest quality. Can I see the key a moment?
